column1: #Text=The New Orleans Pelicans defeated the Minnesota Timberwolves , 122 - 106 , at Target Center on Friday .
#Text=These are two teams going in opposite directions and this result shows just that .

column1: #Text=Defense was key for the Pelicans , as they held the Timberwolves to 46 percent from the field and 22 percent from three - point range .
#Text=Rebounding was a huge factor as well , with the Pelicans winning that battle , 43 - 34 .
#Text=Anthony Davis led the Timberwolves in scoring with 42 points on 16 - of - 22 from the field and 8 - of - 11 from the free - throw line .
#Text=Jrue Holiday was second on the team , as he tallied 25 points , six rebounds and 12 assists .
#Text=Buddy Hield was second on the team , as he dropped 17 points on 7 - of - 10 shooting .
#Text=Gorgui Dieng finished with eight points , eight rebounds and three steals .
#Text=Buddy Hield led Minnesota in scoring , as he provided 17 points and four rebounds on 7 - of - 10 from the field .
#Text=Gorgui Dieng amassed eight points , eight rebounds and three steals .

#Text=The Pelicans ( 21 - 33 ) have been one of the worst teams in the league , as this marks their 17th win at Verizon Center .
